description:
Create src/components/tick-board.ts as the root web component:

@customElement('tick-board')
export class TickBoard extends LitElement {
  @state() ticks: Tick[] = [];
  @state() selectedEpic: string = '';
  @state() searchTerm: string = '';
  @state() activeColumn: string = 'blocked';
  @state() isMobile = window.matchMedia('(max-width: 480px)').matches;
}

Also create src/contexts/board-context.ts:
- Define BoardState interface
- Create boardContext using Lit's createContext
- Set up @provide decorator in tick-board

Register component in main.ts, add <tick-board> to index.html

Test: Component renders, context is available to child components
